laboratory_examinations.findings: The cecum is atypically located in the mid upper abdomen, normal in caliber, with marginal mucosal hyperenhancement and possible mild periappendiceal fat stranding. The appendix is prominent measuring up to 9 mm (top normal), with similar findings.
